    <section>
        <title>About predictors</title>
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160922T160546+0200" comment="Copied from Launchpad: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/dhis2/+spec/predictors"?>
        <para>Predictors are data elements automatically generated from samples of current and past
            data. The most immediate application of predictors is in the simplification of
            monitoring or surveillance rules which allows them to be specified as simple validation
            rules. A predictor specifies an expression and a set of *sample constraints* (identical
            to the current implementation of validation rules). This includes a period type,
            organisation unit levels, and parameters specifying past or periodic sample
            windows.</para>
        <?oxy_comment_end?>
        <para>You use predictors to analyse previous data to predict future values, for example for
            disease surveillance.</para>
        <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app, you manage the following
            predictor objects:</para>
